page_title: 'Using your data with Azure OpenAI Service'
page_description: Use this article to learn about using your data for better text generation in Azure OpenAI.
chunk_title: Deploy to a copilot (preview) or web app
chunk_content: Deploy to a copilot (preview) or web app After you connect Azure OpenAI to your data, you can deploy it using the Deploy to button in Azure OpenAI studio.:::image type="content" source="../media/use-your-data/deploy-model.png" alt-text="A screenshot showing the model deployment button in Azure OpenAI Studio." lightbox="../media/use-your-data/deploy-model.png":::This gives you the option of deploying a standalone web app for you and your users to interact with chat models using a graphical user interface. See Use the Azure OpenAI web app for more information. You can also deploy to a copilot in Copilot Studio (preview) directly from Azure OpenAI studio, enabling you to bring conversational experiences to various channels such as: Microsoft Teams, websites, Dynamics 365, and other Azure Bot Service channels. The tenant used in the Azure OpenAI service and Copilot Studio (preview) should be the same. For more information, see Use a connection to Azure OpenAI On Your Data.> [!NOTE]> Deploying to a copilot in Copilot Studio (preview) is only available in US regions.
